      "instruction": "<p>Add 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span><strong> flour</strong> to the pan and give everything a good mix up</p><p>Add 250ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[350ml]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [450ml]</span><strong> boiled water</strong> with your <strong>vegetable stock mix</strong>, <strong>soft cheese</strong>, <strong>grated cheddar</strong>, 1/3<strong> </strong>of your <strong>grated Italian hard cheese</strong> (you'll use the rest later!) and your <strong>Dijon mustard</strong></p><p>Add your <strong>Chinese rice wine</strong> and mix it all together and cook for 6-7 min – this is your <strong>creamy leek & potato mixture</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
